
// This Hyperlambda code uses the [if] slot to check if the value of the [.condition] node is equal to "yes". If true, it executes the [.lambda] block, which sets the value of the [.result] node to "Condition Met". The [eq] slot is used for equality comparison, and [set-value] assigns the specified value to the target node.
if
   eq:x:@.condition
      .:yes
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.result
         .:Condition Met
